<br>
<br>
In due course everyone was gathered on Command and the request was made.  Alan loked at Melody.  &quot;It's up to you, Melody.&quot;<br>
<br>
Melody smiled at Beka.  &quot;You wanna know if we're related or not.  So do I.  I think it'd be cool if we were, don't you?&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Unh-hunh.  Look, let's be sure.  Rommie, I want thorough testing done and the results double and triple checked.&quot;<br>
<br>
Rommie nodded.  &quot;Of course.  I'll do a three way DNA profile.  I'll need hair, skin and blood samples from you both.&quot;<br>
<br>
Beka looked unhappy.  It got to Harper.  &quot;Hey Rom-Doll, check mine too.  Why not?  I'm sorry, Boss, for all the you know.&quot;<br>
<br>
Beka smiled at him.  &quot;It's O.K.  I understand and i'm sorry about punching you.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;It's O.K.  I guess i had it coming.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;You did.&quot;<br>
<br>
&quot;Hey!'<br>
*************************************************<br>
Rommie and Trance ran the tests.  They checked over and over.  Finally they looked at each other.  Rommie shook her head.  &quot;Well, that's a surprise.  I ceertainly wasn't expecting that.&quot;<br>
<br>
Trance agreed.  &quot;Neither was I.  But we should go tell them.  They'll want to know.&quot;<br>
<br>
So they left Medical and headed back to Command.  Beka jumped up.  &quot;Well?&quot;<br>
<br>
Trance cleared her throat.  Um--well, it looks like you and Melody have matching DNA.  98% in fact.  Which probably means you're a direct descendant from Melody.&quot; <p>Mary Rose<br>
